{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d2dc831a-f666-44f7-b010-5609c4bdd6a6","content":"Here's the report. Your source files (excluding `obj/` and `bin/`) are **Program.cs** and **Services/DataService.cs**. `Program.cs` is just the entry point — the real concerns are in `DataService.cs`.\n\n### Static Dependencies in `DataService.cs`\n\n| Line | Call | Category | Why it hurts testability |\n|------|------|----------|--------------------------|\n| 7 | `DateTime.UtcNow` | Clock | Non-deterministic; tests can't control time |\n| 8 | `Path.Combine(…)` | File system | Pure function — **safe, no wrapping needed** |\n| 9 | `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(…)` | Environment | Couples tests to machine env vars |\n| 12 | `File.WriteAllText(…)` | File I/O | Side-effect: writes to disk |\n| 14 | `Console.WriteLine(…)` | Console I/O | Side-effect: writes to stdout |\n| 19 | `Directory.GetFiles(…)` | File I/O | Reads real file system |\n| 22 | `File.ReadAllText(…)` | File I/O | Reads real file system |\n\n### Recommended Abstractions\n\n1. **`IClock`** — wrap `DateTime.UtcNow`\n2. **`IFileSystem`** — wrap `File.WriteAllText`, `File.ReadAllText`, `Directory.GetFiles` (or use the existing `System.IO.Abstractions` NuGet package)\n3. **`IEnvironment`** — wrap `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable`\n4. **`IConsole`** (optional) — wrap `Console.WriteLine`, or just capture output in tests via `StringWriter`\n\n`Path.Combine` is a pure function with no side effects — no need to abstract it.\n\nWould you like me to implement any of these wrapper interfaces and refactor `DataService` to use them?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c7113ef9-4178-44bf-bc2d-e54eac4d39bf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The grep for \"static\" only found the `Main` method, but the user is asking about static dependencies - meaning calls to static methods/properties on framework types. Let me look more carefully at the source files.\n\nIn `DataService.cs`, I can see several static dependencies